## What Problem This Solves

Fixes an issue where ClickClack channel token `exec` SecretRefs are treated as "not configured" at runtime, despite being valid and resolvable via `openclaw secrets audit --allow-exec`.

Closes #98428

## Why This Change Was Made

`resolveClickClackToken` in `extensions/clickclack/src/accounts.ts` only handled `configured_unavailable` refs with `source === "env"`. For `exec`/`file` SecretRefs, `mode: "inspect"` could not resolve the value at inspection time, and the function silently returned `""`, causing the ClickClack channel to report as not configured.

The fix adds a retry path: when `mode: "inspect"` returns `configured_unavailable` for a non-env source, re-call `resolveSecretInputString` with `mode: "strict"` to trigger the configured secret provider's runtime resolution. If it succeeds, the resolved value is returned. If it fails, the function still returns `""` (unchanged fallback).

## User Impact

ClickClack users with `exec` or `file` SecretRef tokens can now start the channel without wrapper scripts or env-var bridges. `env` SecretRefs are unaffected.

## Evidence

### Code — before

`extensions/clickclack/src/accounts.ts:70-94` (before):

```ts
if (resolved.status !== "available") {
  if (resolved.status === "configured_unavailable" && resolved.ref.source === "env") {
    // ... env-specific resolution
  }
  return "";  // ← exec/file refs silently return empty
}
```

### Code — after

```ts
if (resolved.status !== "available") {
  if (resolved.status === "configured_unavailable" && resolved.ref.source === "env") {
    // ... env-specific resolution (unchanged)
  }
  if (resolved.status === "configured_unavailable") {
    // Non-env SecretRefs (exec, file) — retry with strict mode
    try {
      const strict = resolveSecretInputString({ ..., mode: "strict" });
      if (strict.status === "available") {
        return normalizeResolvedSecretInputString({ value: strict.value, ... }) ?? "";
      }
    } catch {
      // Resolution failed — return empty so caller reports not configured
    }
  }
  return "";
}
```
